      P2 Mission Statement
      wpeA.gif (38909 bytes)

      The NASA Acquisition Pollution Prevention (AP2)   Office was
      established by NASA Headquarters, Code JE, to identify and achieve
      mutually beneficial P2 projects, seeking common P2 goals for NASA
      centers and Department of Defense partners.

      The AP2 Program Office effort seeks to assist in identifying,
      validating and implementing qualified, less hazardous materials and
      processes.

      This approach encourages partnering, leveraging limited resources,
      avoiding duplication of effort and reducing total cost of process
      ownership related to alternative development.

   P2 Methodology and Goals

        * Identifying common needs and criteria of alternatives
        * Identify potential alternatives
        * Determine engineering performance requirements
        * Reduce hazardous material usage in manufacturing, maintenance and
          institutional processes

   Office Profile

      NASA AP2 Office consists of a NASA Civil Servant Program Manager
      and contractor support provided by International Trade Bridge (ITB)
      employees and Dynamac employees.  The value added to this joint venture
      is all participants bring a significant wealth of knowledge and
      expertise to the program.

   Contact Information

      Should you have program questions concerning this Office, please
      contact:

      NASA AP2 Program Manager: Barry M. Braden

      Telephone: 321/867-9134

      FAX: 321/867-8398

      Electronic mail: BradeBM@kscems.ksc.nasa.gov
